index_terms: CHICAGO MILWAUKEE ST PAUL PACIFIC RAILROAD
summary: An ordinance granting the Oregon-Washington Railroad & Navigation Company, the Great Northern Railway Company, the Northern Pacific Railway Company, and the Chicago, Milwaukee & St. Paul Railway Company, and to any one or more of them, their successors and assigns, a right of way for, and the right, privilege and authority to locate, lay down, construct, maintain and operate until December 31, 1950, sundry railway tracks along and across sundry streets, avenues, alleys and other public places within the City of Seattle.
